Threat Hunting Approach
1. Defined a threat hunting hypothesis
2. Enabled endpoint telemetry using Sysmon
3. Simulated attacker behavior using encoded PowerShell
4. Analyzed Sysmon logs for suspicious activity
5. Mapped findings to MITRE ATT&CK techniques
6. Documented findings and assessment

 MITRE ATT&CK Techniques Covered
 T1059.001 – PowerShell
 T1027 – Obfuscated Files or Information

 Key Findings
 Encoded PowerShell execution was observed via Sysmon Event ID 1
 Such behavior is commonly associated with living off the land attacks
This activity warrants further investigation in enterprise environments

